<body
background="http://167.193.53.2/EPD/Pcb/images/seal160s.gif">
<p align="left"><font size="5"><strong>NOTICE OF POSTPONED DATE
FOR BOARD<br>
CONSIDERATION OF PROPOSED RULE REVISIONS<br>
</strong></font><br>
<br clear="all">
<strong>The Environmental Protection Division (EPD) of the
Georgia Department of Natural Resources previously provided
public notice as to proposed revisions to the Georgia Rules and
Regulations for Radioactive Materials, Chapter 391-3-17.
Specifically, EPD previously announced proposed revisions to
amend Rules .01 Standard Provisions, .02 Licensing of Radioactive
Materials, .03 Standards for Protection Against Radiation, .04
Special Radiation Safety Requirements of Radiographic Operations,
.05 Use of Radionuclides in the Healing Arts, .06 Transportation
of Radioactive Material, .07 Notices, Instructions and Reports to
Workers; Inspections, and .10 Administration.Amended. Previous
public notices stated that these proposed rule revisions would be
considered for adoption by the Board of Natural Resources at its
meeting on December 4, 1996. </strong></p>
<p align="left"><strong>EPD hereby provides public notice that
the previously announced proposed rule revisions to the Georgia
Rules and Regulations for Radioactive Materials, Chapter 391-3-17
(as referenced above), will not be considered for adoption by the
Board of Natural Resources at its December 4, 1996 meeting as
previously announced. EPD will follow up with another public
notice as soon as it is determined when the Board will consider
proposed revisions to the Georgia Rules and Regulations for
Radioactive Materials, Chapter 391-3-17.</strong></p>
<p align="left"><strong>For further information, please contact
EPD by calling Thomas E. Hill, Manager, Radioactive Materials
Program at (404) 362-2675.</strong></p>
</body>
</html>
