<h1>Welcome to the Coastal Resources Division</h1>

<h2>Georgia Department of Natural Resouces</h2>

<h3>Duane Harris, Director</h3>

<p><img src="art/rainbow.gif" width="540" height="4"> </p>

<pre>
		Coastal Resources Division
		One Conservation Way
		Brunswick, GA 31523-8600

<img src="art/phone.gif" width="40" height="40"><em> (912)264-7218</em>	Fax:(912)262-3143
</pre>

<hr>

<pre>
	The <em>Coastal Resources Division</em> has primary
responsibility for managing Georgia's marshes, beaches, and
marine fishery resources.  Based in Brunswick, CRD adminsters
permitting programs under the Coastal Marshlands Protection
Act and Shore Protection Act; issues revocable licenses for
state-owned water bottoms; monitors coastal water quality; and
manages shellfish harvest areas.  CRD conducts research;
management and development activities associated with
recreational and commercial fishery resources; represents
Georgia on regional marine fishery boards and commissions;
and builds boat ramps, artificial reefs, and fishing piers.
CRD employs more than 50 persons, has an annual budget of about
$4 million, and is comprised of three work units; the
<b>Ecological Services Section</b>, the <b>Marine Fisheries
Section</b>, and <b>Administration</b>.

</pre>

<p><a href="ecol/index.htm"><b>Ecological Services Section</b> </a></p>

<p><img src="art/red.gif" width="17" height="17"> <em>Coastal
management, habitat management, and permit procedures.</em></p>

<p><a href="fish/index.htm"><b>Marine Fisheries Section</b> </a></p>

<pre>
<img src="art/red.gif" width="17" height="17"><em> Commercial and recreational fisheries management. </em></pre>

<p><a href="admin/index.htm"><b>Administration </b></a></p>

<pre>
