<head>
<title> Federal Aid Coordination Homepage </title>
</head>

<body>

<h1> Federal Aid Coordination </h1>

<h2> Marine Fisheries Section </h2>

<h3> Ron Michaels, Federal Aid Coordinator</h3>

<p>Email: <a href="mailto:ram@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us">
ram@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us </a></p>

<p> Phone: (912)264-7218 <img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
     Federal aid coordination encompasses proposal and contractual preparation and processing;
budget formulation, monitoring, and amendments preparation; and oversight of reporting
compliance with grant obligations for seven Marine Fisheries Section grants.  They are:

     1) South Atlantic Fishery Management Council - Provide technical assistance to the South
Atlantic Fishery Management Council in the development, implementation, and monitoring of
fishery management plans and amendments to enhance fisheries management in the South
Atlantic through State/Council cooperative management of the fisheries occurring in the
Territorial Sea and Economic Exclusive Zone (EEZ). <em> $30,000 Federal </em>

     2) Georgia/NMFS Regional Cooperative Statistics Program - To provide NMFS with the
harvest in pounds, and the ex-vessel and processed value (dollars) of all commercial marine
fishery resources landed in Georgia.  To satisfy data requests for commercial fisheries information
from these data sets.  To also provide NMFS with biostatistical and associated effort data on
certain commercial finfish species.  To provide finfish landings on a weekly or daily basis as
needed for species that are under federal fishery quotas. <em> $135,000 Federal </em> 

     3) Marine Fisheries Research, Surveys, and Development (USFWS/SFR) - Offshore
Bottom Survey, Annual Assessment of Red Drum Exploitation and Stock Structure, Identification
of Gag Spawning Aggregations, Spotted Seatrout Assessment, Socio-Economic Analysis of
Georgia's Marine Recreational Fishery, Offshore Fishing Reef Development &amp; Maintenance,
Inshore Fishing Reef Development &amp; Maintenance, and Fishing Pier/Platform Development &amp;
Maintenance.<em> $392,196 Federal / $130,733 State </em>

     4) Boating Access for Coastal Georgia Anglers (USFWS/SFR) - To provide new or
improved boating access to Georgia's coastal boating anglers.  To also help meet the State's
12.5% boating access obligation within each five-year period. <em> $116,681 Federal / $38,894 State </em>


     5) Fishery-Independent Assessment of Sub-Adult Red Drum in the South Atlantic Bight
(MARFIN/NMFS) - Conduct regional fishery-independent sampling and mark-recapture
experiments to provide the data needed for assessment of the South Atlantic Bight (SAB) stocks
of red drum.  Secondary goals and objectives include further refinement of red drum stock
identification in the SAB, characterization of emigration and escapement from estuarine waters
to the EEZ, and a fishery-independent index of abundance for age 0 red drum. <em> $181,871 Federal /
$28,566 State </em>

     6) Assessment of Georgia's Marine Fishery Resources (IJ/NMFS) - To determine the
relative abundance, size composition, and reproductive status of Georgia's penaeid shrimp and
blue crab stocks.  Monthly fisheries-independent assessment sampling data are used to evaluate
stock status and to develop recommendations for optimum management of these important marine
resources.<em> $25,495 Federal / $8,498 State </em>

     7) Interstate Fisheries Management Planning and Implementation (ACFCMA/NMFS) -
Increase the precision level of bycatch estimates of finfish species in the commercial penaeid
shrimp trawl fishery in Georgia waters and in the EEZ off Georgia.  Provide samples for
determining the age and genetic structure of selected species occurring in the bycatch.  Collect
fishery-independent data in the inshore and nearshore waters of Georgia to compare catch rates
of selected species to rates observed during similar work in the early 1970s, and to provide
reference and supplemental collections for bycatch characterization work.  Also provide
administrative support to the State of Georgia for meeting the public information, regulatory,
legislative, and technical deliberation needs generated by the ACFCMA. <em> $89,220 Federal</em>

</pre>

<p><img src="art/green.gif"><a href="fasrp.htm"> Federal Aid in
Sportfish Restoration</a></p>

<p> <img src="art/blue_bar.gif"></p>

