<head>
<title>Ecological Services Section Homepage</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1> Welcome to the Ecological Services Section </h1>

<h2>Coastal Resources Division, Georgia Dept. of Natural
Resources</h2>

<h3>Dr. Stuart Stevens, Section Chief</h3>

<p>Email: <a href="mailto:stuart@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us">
stuart@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us </a></p>

<p> Phone: (912)264-7218</p>

<p> <img src="art/archipelago.gif"></p>

<p> The Ecological Services Section is responsible for the
management of Georgia's marshes and beaches through permitting
and licensing, water quality monitoring, and coastal area
management programs. The Ecological Services Section was formed
in 1991 by combining the Marsh and Beach Section with the
Shellfish Sanitation Program of the Marine Fisheries Section. The
Section is coordinated through four primary programs: Coastal
Management Program, Enviromental Health Program, Habitat
Management Program, and Operations Program. These programs are
complimented by four federally-funded projects: Altamaha River
Watershed Project, Marina Pumpout Project, Section 401 Water
Quality Certification Assumption Project, and Wetlands Education
Project.</p>

<p> <a href="newczm.htm">COASTAL MANAGEMENT PROGRAM</a></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
<img src="art/green.gif"><em> Development of federally-
approvable Coastal Zone Management Plan</em></pre>

<p> <a href="ehp.htm">ENVIRONMENTAL HEALTH PROGRAM </a></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
<img src="art/green.gif"><em> Monitoring of coastal water
quality and managing shellfish harvest areas </em></pre>

<p> <a href="hmp.htm">HABITAT MANAGEMENT PROGRAM </a></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
<img src="art/green.gif"><em> Administers permitting
programs for marsh and beach areas
and issues revocable licenses for state-
owned water bottoms </em></pre>

<p> <a href="opr.htm">OPERATIONS MANAGEMENT PROGRAM</a></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
<img src="art/green.gif"><em> Grants management, personnel administration,
 and resource management</em></pre>

<p> </p>

<hr>
<strong>

<p>FEDERAL GRANT PROJECTS:</strong></p>

<p> <a href="alt.htm"> Altamaha River Watershed Project </a></p>

<p> <a href="mpo.htm"> Marina Pumpout Project </a></p>

<p> <a href="401.htm"> Section 401 Assumption Project </a></p>

<p> <a href="wet.htm"> Wetlands Education Project </a></p>

<p> <img src="art/island.gif"></p>

<p> <a href="../index.htm">Back to the CRD Homepage </a> </p>

<p> </p>
</body>
