<head>
<title> Marine Fisheries Section Homepage </title>
</head>

<body>

<h1> Welcome to the Marine Fisheries Section</h1>

<h2> Coastal Resources Division, Georgia Dept. of Natural
Resources </h2>

<h3>Susan Shipman, Section Chief</h3>

<p>Email: <a href="mailto:s2@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us">
s2@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us </a></p>

<p> Phone: (912)264-7218</p>

<p> <img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> <img src="art/clipart.gif"></p>

<p> The <em>Marine Fisheries Section</em> has been an integral
component of Coastal Resources Division since its creation in
1978. Formerly the Coastal Fisheries Section under the Game and
Fish Division, the Section historically conducted management
activities (stock monitoring and regulatory actions) almost
exclusively in support of the state's multimillion dollar
commercial fisheries. In the 1970's the Section expanded its
focus into inshore and offshore recreational fisheries. The
offshore artificial reef program began in the early 70's,
followed by the initiation of ongoing life history and stock
assessment studies of Georgia's most important marine sportfishes
in the late 70's. With the transfer of the Section into the
Coastal Resources Division, these activities were continued as
activities of three more comprehensive Programs: <b>Outer
Continental Shelf</b>, <b>Recreational Fisheries</b>, and <b>Commercial
Fisheries</b>. An <b>Administrative Work Unit</b> provides
support sevices to these programs. </p>

<p> <a href="ocs.htm">OUTER CONTINENTAL SHELF PROGRAM</a></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
<img src="art/green.gif"><em> Offshore artificial reef development, saltwater records,
and offshore finfish research</em></pre>

<p> <a href="rec.htm">RECREATIONAL FISHERIES PROGRAM</a></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
<img src="art/green.gif"><em> Sportfish life history research, inshore artificial reef
development, and access enhancements</em></pre>

<p> <a href="comm.htm">COMMERCIAL FISHERIES PROGRAM</a></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
<img src="art/green.gif"><em> Finfish bycatch chracterization and shrimp and crab stock
assessment and monitoring </em></pre>

<p> <a href="work.htm">ADMINISTRATIVE WORK UNIT</a></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
<img src="art/green.gif"><em> Program support inclusive of interjurisdictional fisheries
management and federal aid coordination</em></pre>

<p> <img src="art/blue_bar.gif"></p>

<p> <a href="../index.htm">Back to the CRD Homepage</a></p>

<p> </p>
</body>
