<head>
<title> CRD Publications </title>
</head>

<body>

<p><img src="/CRD/art/library2.gif"></p>

<h1>Publications Information</h1>

<h2> Coastal Resources Division, Georgia Dept. of Natural
Resources </h2>

<p><img src="/CRD/art/color_swirl.gif"></p>

<p> </p>

<pre>
	For more imformation or to obtain the following
publications please contact Michelle Aldenderfer, Senior 
Public Information Specialist.
</pre>

<p><img src="/CRD/art/phone.gif"><em> (912)264-7218</em></p>

<p> email: <a href="mailto:michelle@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us">
michelle@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us</a></p>

<p> </p>

<hr>

<h2>Brochures/Magazines</h2>

<pre>     
&quot;Careful Catch&quot; - Information on responsible angling in coastal
 waters.

&quot;How to Catch, Clean, and Cook a Blue Crab&quot; - Information on
 recreational crabbing.

&quot;Georgia Sound&quot; - Quarterly newsletter reporting on the developing
 Georgia Coastal Management Program as well as other coastal
 Georgia issues.

&quot;Georgia Coastal Managmeent Program&quot; - Informational brochure on
 the developing Program.

&quot;Georgia Safe Boating Guide&quot; - Information on responsible boating
 techniques.

&quot;Georgia Shellfish&quot; - Information on how to harvest, store and
 cook shellfish.

&quot;Manatees in Georgia&quot; - Information on this endangered marine
 mammal living in Georgia waters.

&quot;Georgia's Wetlands&quot; - Information on importance of wetland
 preservation.

&quot;Southeast Wetlands&quot; - A detailed report on the status of
 wetlands in the Southeast.

&quot;Earth Day Nature Trail Guide&quot; - Trail guide to the nature trail
 located on the DNR/CRD property in Brunswick.

&quot;Sapelo Island National Estuarine Research Reserve&quot; - 
 Information on one of Georgia's barrier islands accessible
 by ferry only.

&quot;Stream of Conscience&quot; - Information on solutions for clean
 water pressures.

&quot;Golden Isles of Georgia&quot; - Information on coastal tourism.

&quot;Clean Coast&quot; - Information on non-profit organization called
 Clean Coast, dedicated to keeping beaches clean.

&quot;Official Guide to Golden Isles&quot; - Information on coastal
 tourism.

&quot;Georgia DNR Film &amp; Video Catalog&quot; - A listing and description
 of all videos produced by the Department of Natural Resources. 

&quot;Gray's Reef National Marine Sanctuary&quot; - Information on this
 offshore fishing and diving resource.

&quot;Altamaha River Bioreserve&quot; - Information on this bioreserve
 managed by The Nature Conservancy of Georgia.

&quot;Southeast Adventures&quot; - Inforamtion on outfitter that offers
 sea kayaking trips.
</pre>

<h2>Guides/Regulations</h2>

<pre>

&quot;1996 Fish Consumption Guidelines&quot; - New guidelines based
 on recent data.

&quot;1996 Coastal Georgia Charter Services&quot; - Information on charter
 services offered in coastal Georgia.

&quot;1996 Freshwater and Saltwater Fishing Regulations&quot;
 - Information on regulations and guidelines for Georgia.

&quot;Georgia's Offshore Fishing Guide&quot; - Information on offshore
 fishing and diving locations.

&quot;Georgia Saltwater Access Guide&quot; - Information on where fishing
 access points are along coast including piers, docks and boat ramps.
</pre>

<h2>Posters</h2>

<pre>

Southeast Atlantic Fish

Georgia's Loggerhead Sea Turtles

Right Whales Along the Georgia Coast

Coastal Georgia Map
</pre>

