<h1> Guide to Fishing Access Sites </h1>

<p> </p>

<h2> McIntosh County </h2>

<p><img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> DRIVING DIRECTIONS TO FISHING ACCESS FACILITIES</p>

<p> <em>NON-BOATING FISHING SITES</em></p>

<p> (1) Blue-N-Hall Fishing Dock: Take Exit 10 south on GA HWY
251 for 1.2 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right (south) 0.9 miles to
GA HWY 99. Turn left (north) 4.4 miles to Blue-N-Hall sign. Turn
right and follow dead end road to boat dock.</p>

<p> (2) Champney River Bridge Catwalk: Take Exit 10 south on GA
HWY 251 for 1.2 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right (south) 3.3
miles to Champney River Bridge. Parking area on left past bridge.</p>

<p> (3) Darien Waterfront Dock: Take Exit 10 south on GA HWY 251
for 1.2 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right (south) 1.2 miles to
Broad Street. Turn left before crossing Darien River Bridge.
Immediately after left turn, waterfront dock located on right
behind Welcome Center.</p>

<p> (4) Harris Neck Wildlife Refuge Fishing Dock: Take Exit 12
south on U.S. HWY 17 for 1.0 miles to GA HWY 131. Turn left
(south) 6.2 miles to Harris Neck Creek Bridge near entrance to
Harris Neck Wildlife Refuge. Dock located on left.</p>

<p> (5) Shellman Bluff Fishing Dock: Take Exit 11 south on GA HWY
57 for 1.0 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn left (north) 2.2 miles to
Pine Harbor Road. Turn right 0.1 miles and then turn left on
Shellman Bluff Road and drive 6.8 miles. At stop sign, turn right
toward Southerland Bluff then immediately take first road on left
0.2 miles to Broro River Bluff. Turn left 0.1 miles to dock. Must
have permission to fish off dock. Phone (912) 832-5426.</p>

<p> <em>BOAT RAMPS</em></p>

<p> (6) Barbour River Landing: Take Exit 12 south on U.S. HWY 17
for 1.0 miles to GA HWY 131. Turn left (south) 7.1 miles to end
of Harris Neck Road (HWY 131). Turn left into Harris Neck
Wildlife Refuge on Barbour Landing Road and drive 0.5 miles to
boat ramp. Boat ramp located on right. This facility is closed
during Wood Stork nesting feeding season (March 1 - August 31).
(One single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (7) Bellville Boat Ramp: Take Exit 11 south on GA HWY 57 for
5.1 miles to Bellville Road. Turn left 1.6 miles to boat ramp.
(One single-lane ramp). </p>

<p> (8) Blue-N-Hall Boat Ramp: Take Exit 10 south on GA HWY 251
for 1.2 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right (south) 0.9 miles to GA
HWY 99. Turn left (north) 4.4 miles to Blue-N-Hall Park sign on
right. Turn right and follow dead end road to boat ramp. (One
single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (9) Champney River Boat Ramp: Take Exit 10 south on GA HWY
251 for 1.2 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right (south) 3.3 miles
and cross the Champney River Bridge. Turn left into parking area
at south end of bridge. (One double-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (10) Darien City Boat Ramp: Take Exit 10 south on GA HWY 251
for 1.2 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right (south) 1.2 miles to
Broad Street. Turn right before crossing Darien River Bridge.
Drive approximately 0.1 miles and take first left. Boat ramp
located at bottom of bluff. (One single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (11) Harris Neck Wildlife Refuge Boat Ramp: Take Exit 12
south on U.S. HWY 17 for 1.0 miles to GA HWY 131. Turn left
(south) 6.2 miles to Harris Neck Creek Bridge located at Harris
Neck Wildlife Refuge. Boat ramp located on left after crossing
bridge. Recommended for small boat launching only. (One
single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (12) White Chimney Creek Boat Ramp: Take Exit 11 south on GA
HWY 57 for 1.0 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn left (north) 2.2 miles
to Pine Harbor Road. Turn right 0.1 mile and then turn left on
Shellman Bluff Road for 4.5 miles to ramp located on right across
White Chimney Creek Bridge. (One single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> <em>MARINAS</em></p>

<p> (13) Belle Bluff Marina: Take Exit 11 south on GA HWY 57 for
1.0 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn left (north) 2.2 miles to Pine
Harbor Road. Turn right 0.1 miles and then turn left on Shellman
Bluff Road. Drive 3.0 miles to Belle Hammock Road. Turn right 1.6
miles to Belle Bluff marina sign. Follow dirt road to left for
0.2 miles to marina. Facility provides hoist lift launching
(7,000 lb). Phone: (912) 832-5323.</p>

<p> (14) Dallas Bluff Marina &amp; Campground: Take Exit 11 south
on GA HWY 57 for 1.0 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn left (north) 2.2
miles to Pine Harbor Road. Turn right 0.1 miles and then turn
left on Shellman Bluff Road. Drive 6.8 miles to stop sign. Turn
left and follow road for 1.7 miles to Dallas Bluff Marina sign.
Turn right at sign and follow road for 0.1 miles to marina.
Facility provides hoist lift launching (4,000 lb). Phone: (912)
832-5116.</p>

<p> (15) Fisherman's Lodge: Take Exit 11 south on GA HWY 57 for
1.0 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn left (north) 2.2 miles to Pine
Harbor Road. Turn right 0.1 miles and then turn left on Shellman
Bluff Road. Drive 6.8 miles to stop sign. Turn right toward
Southerland Bluff then immediately take first road on left and
drive 0.2 miles to Broro River Bluff. Turn right drive 0.3 miles
to marina. Facility provides hoist lift launching (11,000 lb).
Phone: (912) 832-5162.</p>

<p> (16) McIntosh Rod and Gun Club: Take Exit 10 south on GA HWY
251 for 1.2 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right (south) 0.9 miles to
GA HWY 99. Turn left (north) 4.4 miles to Blue-N-Hall Park sign
on right. Turn right and follow dead end road to marina. Facility
provides hoist lift launching (6,000 lb). Phone: (912) 437-4677.</p>

<p>. (17) Pine Harbor Marina: Take Exit 11 south on GA HWY 57 for
1.0 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn left (north) 2.2 miles to Pine
Harbor Road. Turn right 2.7 miles to Belle Hammock Road. Turn
onto Belle Hammock Road for 0.1 mile then turn right on Pine
Harbor Marina Road for 0.2 miles to marina. Facility provides
hoist lift launching (6,000 lb). Phone: (912) 832- 5999.</p>

<p> (18) Shellman Bluff Fish Camp: Take Exit 11 south on GA HWY
57 for 1.0 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn left (north) 2.2 miles to
Pine Harbor Road. Turn right 0.1 miles and then turn left on
Shellman Bluff Road. Drive 6.8 miles to stop sign. Turn right
toward Southerland Bluff then immediately take first road on left
and drive 0.2 miles to Broro River Bluff. Turn right on bluff
road and drive 0.2 miles to camp. Facility provides hoist lift
launching (7,000 lb). Phone: (912) 832-4331.</p>

<p> (19) Shellman Bluff Motel: Take Exit 11 south on GA HWY 57
for 1.0 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn left (north) 2.2 miles to Pine
Harbor Road. Turn right 0.1 miles and then turn left on Shellman
Bluff Road. Drive 6.8 miles to stop sign. Turn right toward
Southerland Bluff then immediately take first road on left and
drive 0.2 miles to Broro River Bluff. Turn left on bluff road and
drive 0.1 miles to marina. Facility does not provide launching.
Phone: (912) 832-5426.</p>

