<h1> Guide to Fishing Access Sites </h1>

<p> </p>

<h2> Glynn County </h2>

<p><img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> DRIVING DIRECTIONS FROM INTERSTATE-95</p>

<p> <em>NON-BOATING FISHING SITES</em></p>

<p> (1) Back River East Pier (Brunswick): Take Exit 8 south on
Spur 25 (North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17.
Turn right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons
Island. Turn left (east) 2.0 miles and cross over Back River
Bridge. Pier entrance located across bridge on left side of
Causeway.</p>

<p> (2) Back River West Pier (Brunswick): Take Exit 8 south on
Spur 25 (North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17.
Turn right 1.7 miles to Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons
Island. Turn left (east) 1.5 miles to Back River Bridge. Pier
entrance located on left side of Causeway before bridge. </p>

<p> (3) Blythe Island Regional Park Fishing Dock: Take Exit 6
south on U.S. HWY 17 0.6 miles to GA HWY 303. Turn right (north)
3.6 miles to park entrance located on right. Enter park 1.4 miles
to dock. </p>

<p> (4) Clam Creek Foot Bridge: Take Exit 6 north on U.S. HWY 17
5.0 miles to the Jekyll Island Causeway (GA HWY 50). Turn right
6.3 miles to Beachview Drive. Turn left 4.3 miles to Clam Creek
Road. Turn right to end of road. Footbridge located on northeast
corner of the picnic area. </p>

<p> (5) Gould's Inlet Fishing Dock (East Beach): Take Exit 8
south on Spur 25 (North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to
U.S. HWY 17. Turn right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading
to St. Simons Island. Turn left (east) 4.4 miles to New Sea
Island Drive. Turn right 0.2 miles to King's Way Drive. Turn left
3.8 miles to 1st Street. Note that King's Way Drive becomes Ocean
Blvd. Turn right 0.1 miles to Bruce Drive. Turn left 0.7 miles to
the end of road.</p>

<p> (6) Jekyll Creek Fishing Pier: Take Exit 6 north on U.S. HWY
17 for 5.0 miles to Jekyll Island Causeway (GA HWY 50). Turn
right 5.7 miles to the Jekyll Creek Bridge. Pier located on left
before bridge. (Scheduled completion in late 1996). </p>

<p> (7) Jekyll Island Pier: Take Exit 6 north on U.S. HWY 17 for
5.0 miles to the Jekyll Island Causeway (GA HWY 50). Turn right
6.3 miles to Beachview Drive. Turn left 4.3 miles to Clam Creek
Road. Turn right to end of road. </p>

<p> (8) Little River Bridge Catwalk: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25
(North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn
right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons
Island. Turn left (east) 2.4 miles to Little River Bridge. Pier
entrance located before crossing bridge on right.</p>

<p> (9) MacKay River East Pier: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25
(North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn
right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons
Island. Turn left (east) 3.7 miles which includes crossing the
MacKay River Bridge. Pier entrance located approximately 0.3
miles past the MacKay River Bridge on right side of Causeway.
Turn right (U-turn) onto side road and drive back toward bridge.</p>

<p> (10) MacKay River West Pier: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25
(North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn
right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons
Island. Turn left (east) 2.8 miles to MacKay River Bridge. Pier
entrance located before bridge on right.</p>

<p> (11) Overlook Park Fishing Dock: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25
(North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn
right (south) 2.4 miles. Park located on left side of U.S. HWY
17. (Limited fishing access during low tide.) </p>

<p> (12) St. Simons Island Pier: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25
(North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn
right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons
Island. Turn left (east) 4.4 miles to New Sea Island Drive. Turn
right 0.2 miles to King's Way Drive. Turn left 2.2 miles to
Mallory Street. Turn right 0.2 miles to pier.</p>

<p> <em>BOAT RAMPS</em></p>

<p> (13) Blythe Island Beach Drive Park Boat Ramp: Take Exit 6
south on U.S. HWY 17 for 0.6 miles to GA HWY 303. Turn right
(north) 3.8 miles to Blythe Island Drive. Turn left 1.1 miles to
Park Street. Turn right 0.1 miles. (Two single-lane ramps).</p>

<p> (14) Blythe Island Regional Park Boat Ramp: Take Exit 6 south
on U.S. HWY 17 for 0.6 miles to GA HWY 303. Turn right (north)
3.6 miles to park entrance. Turn right into park entrance, drive
1.4 miles to ramp. (One single-lane ramp). </p>

<p> (15) Jekyll Island Boat Ramp: Take Exit 6 north on U.S. HWY
17 for 5.0 miles to the Jekyll Island Causeway (GA HWY 50). Turn
right 6.5 miles to River View Drive. Turn right 0.6 miles to
Water Ski Park sign. Turn right 0.5 miles on dirt road to ramp.
(One single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (16) MacKay River Boat Ramp: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25
(North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn
right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons
Island. Turn left (east) 3.7 miles and drive across the MacKay
River Bridge. Boat ramp entrance located approximately 0.3 miles
past the MacKay River Bridge on right side of Causeway. Turn
right (U-turn) onto side road and drive back toward bridge. (One
double-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (17) South Brunswick River Boat Ramp: Take Exit 6 south on
U.S. HWY 17 for 0.6 miles to GA HWY 303. Turn right (north) 1.5
miles to the South Brunswick River Bridge. Boat ramp located on
left before crossing bridge. (One single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (18) Turtle River Boat Ramp (GA HWY 303): Take Exit 6 south
on U.S. HWY 17 for 0.6 miles to GA HWY 303. Turn right (north)
5.2 miles to the Turtle River Bridge. Boat ramp located on left
after crossing bridge. (One single-lane ramp). </p>

<p> (19) Village Creek (Harrington) Boat Ramp: Take Exit 8 south
on Spur 25 (North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY
17. Turn right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St.
Simons Island. Turn left (east) 4.4 miles to Sea Island Road.
Turn left 3.1 miles to Frederica Road. Turn left 1.7 miles to
Harrington Drive. Turn right 0.9 miles to end of road. Ramp
located on the right. Ramp located on small creek that is shallow
during low tide. (One single-lane ramp)</p>

<p> <em>MARINAS</em></p>

<p> (20) Blythe Island Regional Park Marina: Take Exit 6 south on
U.S. HWY 17 for 0.6 miles to GA HWY 303. Turn right (north) 3.6
miles to park entrance. Turn right into park entrance, drive 1.2
miles to marina. Facility provides hoist lift launching (8,000
lb). Phone: (912) 261-3805.</p>

<p> (21) Brunswick Landing Marina: Take Exit 7 south on U.S. HWY
341 for 3.7 miles to marina located on right. Facility does not
provide drive-up launching (100,000 lb). Phone: (912) 262-9264.</p>

<p> (22) Brunswick Marina: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25 (North
Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right
(south) 2.4 miles to marina located on left. Facility provides
hoist lift launching (4,500 lb). Phone: (912) 265-2290.</p>

<p> (23) Credle's Fish Camp: Take Exit 6 north on U.S. HWY 17 for
3.0 miles. Look for Credle's sign on right. Turn right on dirt
road and drive 0.3 miles to camp. Facility provides hoist lift
launching (6,000 lb). Phone: (912) 261-1935.</p>

<p> (24) Golden Isles Marina: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25 (North
Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn right 1.7
miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons Island. Turn
left (east) 4.2 miles. Marina located on right before crossing
Frederica River Bridge. Facility does not provide launching.
Phone: (912) 634-1128.</p>

<p> (25) Hampton River Club Marina: Take Exit 8 south on Spur 25
(North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Turn
right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St. Simons
Island. Turn left (east) 4.4 miles to Sea Island Road. Turn left
3.1 miles to Frederica Road. Turn left 2.2 miles to Lawrence
Road. Turn right 6.7 miles to Hampton Marina sign. Turn right 0.2
miles to marina. Facility provides hoist and fork lift launching
(9,000 lb). Phone: (912) 638-1210.</p>

<p> (26) Jekyll Harbor Marina: Take Exit 6 north on U.S. HWY 17
for 5.0 miles to the Jekyll Island Causeway (GA HWY 50). Turn
right 6.5 miles to River View Drive. Turn right 0.1 miles to
Harbor Road. Turn right 0.1 miles to marina entrance. Turn right
0.2 miles to marina. Facility provides fork lift launching
(12,000 lb). Phone: (912) 635-3137.</p>

<p> (27) Jekyll Island Historic (Wharf) Marina: Take Exit 6 north
on U.S. HWY 17 for 5.0 miles to the Jekyll Island Causeway (GA
HWY 50). Turn right 6.5 miles to River View Drive (south). Turn
left and make a U-turn back west on GA HWY 50. Drive back toward
Toll Booth to River View Drive (north). Turn right 0.5 miles to
wharf. Wharf and parking located on left. Facility does not
provide launching. Phone: (912) 635-2891.</p>

<p> (28) St. Simons Boating and Fishing Club: Take Exit 8 south
on Spur 25 (North Golden Isles Expressway) 4.3 miles to U.S. HWY
17. Turn right 1.7 miles to the Torras Causeway leading to St.
Simons Island. Turn left (east) 4.4 miles to the Sea Island Road.
Turn left 0.2 miles to Hamilton Drive. Turn left 0.2 miles to
marina. Facility provides hoist lift launching (8,000 lb). Phone:
