<body>

<h1>Marine Sportfish Creel Survey</h1>

<p> </p>

<h2>Nick Nicholson, Project Leader</h2>

<p> <img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> Fishery-dependent data are important for regional and state
management decision-making. Current levels of effort in the
Marine Recreational Fisheries Statistics Survey (MRFSS) are
inadequate for timely and accurate data collection. The
Recreational Fisheries Program has worked cooperatively with the
MRFSS and plans to renew this effort to expand the number of
intercepts and telephone interviews.</p>

<p> The data provided by an expanded level of effort within the
MRFSS is needed to allow state/regional fishery managers to make
more timely and valid decisions. This will allow more accurate
calculations of coastal fishing pressure and help monitor the
status of Georgia's marine recreational fishery.</p>

<p> <img src="art/blue_bar.gif"></p>

<p> <a href="index.htm">Back to the CRD Homepage</a></p>

<p> </p>
</body>
