<h1> Administrative Work Unit</h1>

<h2> Marine Fisheries Section </h2>

<h3> Susan Shipman, Section Chief</h3>

<p><img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> The Marine Fisheries Section's administrative unit is
comprised of five associates who provide policy, administrative,
clerical, budgetary, personnel and managerial support to a work
unit of approximately 30 associates. Federal-aid coordination,
regulatory compliance with interstate fisheries management plans,
and interjurisdictional fisheries management planning is
accomplished by the administrative team associates working in
concert with the Section's Program Leaders. Federal aid
coordination encompasses proposal and contractual preparation and
processing; budget formulation, monitoring, and amendments
preparation; and oversight of reporting compliance with grant
obligations for seven Marine Fisheries Section grants. Section
associates collaborate with the Section Chief in formulation of
regulations, legislation, issues papers and policy pertaining to
state, interstate, and state/federal marine fisheries management.
The unit serves as the state's principal link with the South
Atlantic Fishery Management Council and the Atlantic States
Marine Fisheries Commission. Unit associates perform a number of
public relations functions as well.</p>

