<h1> Guide to Fishing Access Sites </h1>

<p> </p>

<h2> Chatam County </h2>

<p><img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> DRIVING DIRECTIONS FROM INTERSTATE-95</p>

<p> <em>NON-BOATING FISHING SITES</em></p>

<p> (1) Back River Fishing Pier (Tybee Island): Take Exit 17 east
on I-16 for 7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit
for 0.6 miles to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for
0.8 miles to Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on GA
HWY 204 for 0.3 miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 16.6
miles to Jones Avenue located on Tybee Island. Turn right for 1.6
miles to Chatham Avenue. Turn right for 0.1 miles to Alley Way
Two. Pier located on left at end of alley way. </p>

<p> (2) Bell's Landing Fishing Dock: Take Exit 16 east GA HWY 204
for 7.1 miles. Turn right on Apache Avenue 0.6 miles to end of
avenue. Boat ramp and parking located on left. (scheduled
completion in 1996)</p>

<p> (3) Downing Fishing Piers: Take Exit 16 east on GA HWY 204
for 10.4 miles. Turn right on Montgomery Crossroads 1.2 miles to
Waters Avenue. Turn right 3.3 miles to Moon River Bridge. Note
that Waters Avenue leads into Whitefield Avenue then into Diamond
Causeway leading to Skidaway Island. Fishing piers located on
both sides of river. (scheduled completion in 1998)</p>

<p> (4) Kings Ferry Community Park Fishing Dock: Take Exit 16
east on GA HWY 204 for 2.1 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Take HWY 17
south 2.7 miles. Park located on left before crossing Ogeechee
River Bridge.</p>

<p> (5) Lazaretto Creek Fishing Dock: Take Exit 17 east on I-16
for 7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6
miles to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8
miles to Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on GA HWY
204 for 0.3 miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 13.6 miles to
Lazaretto Creek Boat Ramp located on right. Follow side road past
boat ramp for 0.4 miles to dock.</p>

<p> (6) Salt Creek Park Boat Ramp: Take Exit 16 east on GA HWY
204 for 2.1 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Take HWY 17 north for 4.1
miles. Park located on left just past the Salt Creek Bridge.</p>

<p> (7) Thunderbolt Fishing Pier: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for
7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles
to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on GA HWY 204 for
0.3 miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 2.9 miles to
Mechanics Avenue. Turn left on Mechanics for 0.3 miles. Pier
located at end of avenue. (Scheduled completion in 1996).</p>

<p> (8) Spencer, F.W., Community Park Dock: Take Exit 17 east on
I-16 for 7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for
0.6 miles to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8
miles to Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on GA HWY
204 for 0.3 miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 6.0 miles
to Islands Expressway. Turn left for 1.5 miles. Park located on
right side of Expressway. </p>

<p> <em>BOAT RAMPS</em></p>

<p> (9) Bell's Landing Boat Ramp: Take Exit 16 east on GA HWY 204
for 7.1 miles to Apache Avenue. Turn right for 0.6 miles to end
of avenue. Boat ramp and parking located on left. (One
double-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (10) Houlihan Boat Ramp Park: Take Exit 19 south on GA HWY 30
for 2.7 miles. Turn left and continue south on GA HWY 30 for an
additional 0.9 miles to GA HWY 25. Turn left (north) for 0.8
miles. Park located on right before crossing the Houlihan Bridge
(Savannah River). (Two double-lane ramps).</p>

<p> (11) Kings Ferry Community Park Boat Ramp: Take Exit 16 east
on GA HWY 204 for 2.1 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Take HWY 17 south for
2.7 miles. Park located on left before crossing Ogeechee River
Bridge. (One double-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (12) Lazaretto Creek Boat Ramp: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for
7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles
to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 13.6 miles to the
Lazaretto Creek Boat Ramp. (One double-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (13) Salt Creek Park Boat Ramp: Take Exit 16 east on GA HWY
204 for 2.1 miles to U.S. HWY 17. Take HWY 17 north for 4.1
miles. Park located on left just past the Salt Creek Bridge. Ramp
recommended for small boats only. (One single-lane ramp). </p>

<p> (14) Skidaway Narrows Park Boat Ramp: Take Exit 16 east on GA
HWY 204 for 10.4 miles to Montgomery Crossroads. Turn right 1.2
miles to Waters Avenue. Turn right for 3.9 miles. Park located on
right before crossing draw bridge. (Two triple- lane ramps).</p>

<p> (15) Spencer, F.W., Community Park Boat Ramp: Take Exit 17
east on I-16 for 7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector
Exit for 0.6 miles to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204
for 0.8 miles to Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on
GA HWY 204 for 0.3 miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 6.0
miles to Islands Expressway. Turn left on Islands Expressway and
drive 1.5 miles. Park located on right side of Expressway. (One
double-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (16) Thunderbolt Boat Ramp: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 4.0 miles to Macceo
Drive located past the Wilmington River Bridge. Turn left 0.4
miles to end of Macceo Drive. (One single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> 17) Tybee Island Boat Ramp: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 16.6 miles to Jones Avenue
located on Tybee Island. Turn right 1.6 miles to Chatham Avenue.
Turn right for 0.2 miles to Alley Way 3. Ramp located at end of
alley. Recommended for launching small boats only. (Site includes
beach launching).</p>

<p> <emmarinas</em></p>

<p> (18) Bona Bella Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 2.2 miles to Skidaway
Road. Turn right 1.0 to LaRoche Avenue. Turn left 0.9 miles to
Jasmine Avenue. Turn left and immediately bear right on
Livingston Avenue for 0.4 miles to marina. Facility provides
hoist lift launching (8,000 lb). Phone: (912) 355-9601.</p>

<p> (19) Bull River Yacht Club: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 8.6 miles to club entrance
located on right. Facility does not provide launching. Phone:
(912) 897-7300.</p>

<p> (20) Chimney Creek Fish Camp: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for
7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles
to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 14.8 miles to D.A.V.
Road. Turn right 0.3 miles to marina located on left. Facility
provides hoist lift launching (6,000 lb). Phone: (912) 786-9857.</p>

<p> (21) Coffee Bluff Fish Camp: Take Exit 16 east on GA HWY 204
for 8.9 miles to Holland Drive. Turn right 0.5 miles to White
Bluff Road. Turn right 3.2 miles to marina at end of road. Note
that White Bluff Road becomes Coffee Bluff Road. Facility
provides hoist lift launching (4,000 lb). Phone: (912) 925-9030.</p>

<p> (22) Delegal Creek Marina: Take Exit 16 east on GA HWY 204
for 10.4 miles to Montgomery Crossroads. Turn right 1.2 miles to
Waters Avenue. Turn right 5.2 miles to security gate. Note that
Waters Avenue leads into Whitefield Avenue then into Diamond
Causeway leading to Skidaway Island. Enter security gate and
request information to marina. Facility does not provide
launching. Phone: (912) 598-0023.</p>

<p> (23) Fountain Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8 miles
to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to 37th
Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to Abercorn
Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3 miles to
U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 3.2 miles to River Drive. Turn
right 0.2 miles to marina located on left. Facility does not
provide drive-up launching (9,000 lb). Phone: (912) 354-2283</p>

<p> (24) Hogan's Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8 miles
to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to 37th
Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to Abercorn
Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3 miles to
U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 4.9 miles to Johnny Mercer Blvd.
Turn right 2.9 miles to Wilmington Island Road. Road to marina
located immediately on right after turning onto Wilmington Island
Road. Facility provides hoist and fork lift launching (15,000
lb). Phone: (912) 897-3474.</p>

<p> (25) Isle of Hope Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 2.2 miles to Skidaway
Road. Turn right for 1.0 to LaRoche Avenue. Turn left for 3.4
miles to Bluff Road. Right on Bluff Road 0.4 miles to marina.
Facility provides hoist lift launching (8,000 lb). Phone: (912)
354-8187.</p>

<p> (26) Landings Harbor: Take Exit 16 east on GA HWY 204 for
10.4 miles to Montgomery Crossroads. Turn right 1.2 miles to
Waters Avenue. Turn right for 5.2 miles to McWhorter Drive. Note
that Waters Avenue leads into Whitefield Avenue then into Diamond
Causeway leading to Skidaway Island. Turn left on McWhorter Drive
for 1.7 miles to the Landings security gate located on right.
Enter security gate and request information to marina. Facility
provides fork lift launching (8,000 lb). Phone: (912) 598-1901.</p>

<p> (27) Lazaretto Creek Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for
7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles
to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 14.2 miles just past
Lazaretto Creek Bridge. Turn right and follow narrow road for 0.2
miles to marina. Facility does not provide launching. Phone:
(912) 786-5848.</p>

<p> (28) Lee Shore Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 4.9 miles to Johnny Mercer
Blvd. Turn right for 2.7 miles. Lee Shore Marina is located on
the right just past bridge. Facility does not provide launching.
Phone: (912) 897-1154.</p>

<p> (29) Marlin Marina (formally Tybee Marina): Take Exit 17 east
on I-16 for 7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit
for 0.6 miles to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for
0.8 miles to Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY
204 for 0.3 miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 16.6 miles to
Jones Avenue located on Tybee Island. Turn right 1.3 miles to
14th Street. Turn right 0.3 miles to Chatham Avenue. Marina
located across Chatham Avenue to the left. Facility provides
hoist lift launching (4,000 lb). Phone: (912) 786-7508.</p>

<p> (30) Palmer-Johnson (formally Thunderbolt Marina): Take Exit
17 east on I-16 for 7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector
Exit for 0.6 miles to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204
for 0.8 miles to Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on
HWY 204 for 0.3 miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 3.2
miles to River Drive. Turn right 0.6 miles to marina located on
left. Facility does not provide drive-up launching (300,000 lb).
Phone: (912) 352-4956.</p>

<p> (31) Riverwatch Marina (formally Ambos Marina): Take Exit 17
east on I-16 for 7.8 miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector
Exit for 0.6 miles to 37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204
for 0.8 miles to Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on
HWY 204 for 0.3 miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 3.2 miles
to River Drive. Turn right 0.3 miles to marina located on left.
Facility does not provide drive-up launching (25,000 lb). Phone:
(912) 354-4133.</p>

<p> (32) Sail Harbor Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) 4.9 miles to Johnny Mercer
Blvd. Turn right 2.9 miles to Wilmington Island Road. Turn right
for 1.2 miles to marina entrance on right. Facility does not
provide launching. Phone: (912) 897-2896.</p>

<p> (33) Savannah Bend Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) and drive 3.8 miles. Take
first left turn past Wilmington River Bridge. Follow narrow paved
road for 0.2 miles to Marina. Facility does not provide drive-up
launching (12,000 lb). Phone: (912) 897-3625.</p>

<p> (34) Tidewater Boat Works: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 3.0 miles to Mechanics
Avenue. Turn left 0.5 miles to end of road. Marina located on
right. Facility does not provide drive-up launching (50,000 lb).
Phone: (912) 352-1335.</p>

<p> (35) Tuten's Fish Camp: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8
miles to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to
37th Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to
Abercorn Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3
miles to U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 2.2 miles to Skidaway
Road. Turn right 1.0 miles to LaRoche Avenue. Turn left 2.6 miles
to marina located on left. Facility provides hoist lift launching
(3,000 lb). Phone: (912) 355-8747.</p>

<p> (36) Young's Marina: Take Exit 17 east on I-16 for 7.8 miles
to Exit 35. Take 37th St. Connector Exit for 0.6 miles to 37th
Street. Turn left (west) on GA HWY 204 for 0.8 miles to Abercorn
Street. Turn right and continue west on HWY 204 for 0.3 miles to
U.S. HWY 80. Turn left (east) for 4.9 miles to Johnny Mercer
Blvd. Turn right 2.9 miles to Wilmington Island Road. Turn right
0.6 miles to marina entrance on right. Facility provides hoist
lift launching (4,000 lb). Phone: (912) 897-2608.</p>

