<h1> Guide to Fishing Access Sites </h1>

<p> </p>

<h2> Liberty County </h2>

<p><img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> DRIVING DIRECTIONS FROM INTERSTATE-95</p>

<p> <em>NON-BOATING FISHING SITES</em></p>

<p> (1) Riceboro Creek Fishing Docks: Take Exit 12 north on U.S.
HWY 17 for 6.8 miles. Two docks located on Riceboro Creek.</p>

<p> (2) Sunbury Fishing Dock: Take Exit 13 east on GA HWY 38 for
4.4 miles to Fort Morris Road. Turn left 3.1 miles to Stevens
Road. Turn right 0.3 miles to dock. (Scheduled completion in
1996)</p>

<p> <em>BOAT RAMPS</em></p>

<p> (3) Liberty County Regional Park Boat Ramp: Take Exit 13 west
on GA HWY 38 for 1.5 miles to Isle Of Right Road. Turn right 1.9
miles to park located on right before crossing Jones Creek
Bridge. Recommended for small boat launching only. (One
single-lane ramp).</p>

<p> (4) Sunbury Boat Ramp: Take Exit 13 east on GA HWY 38 for 4.4
miles to Fort Morris Road. Turn left 3.1 miles to Stevens Road.
Turn right 0.3 miles to boat ramp. (One double-lane ramp).</p>

<p> <em>MARINAS</em></p>

<p> (5) Half Moon Marina: Take Exit 13 east on GA HWY 38 for 7.3
miles to Kings Road. Turn right 1.2 miles to Azalea Road. Turn
right 0.1 miles to marina located on right. Facility provides
hoist lift launching (8,000 lb). Phone: (912) 884-5819.</p>

<p> (6) Yellow Bluff Fish Camp: Take Exit 13 east on GA HWY 38
for 9.8 miles to Yellow Bluff Road. Turn right 0.2 miles to fish
camp. Facility provides hoist lift launching (4,500 lb). Phone:
(912) 884-5448.</p>

