<body>

<h1>Sportfish Stock Assessment / Life History</h1>

<p> </p>

<h2>Recreational Fisheries Program</h2>

<p> <img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> <img src="art/ftp_fish.gif"></p>

<p> Red drum and spotted seatrout are the most targeted inshore
marine sportfish in coastal Georgia. Previous research indicates
that each estuarine system has an individual population of
spotted seatrout and immature red drum. Biotelemetry studies have
revealed that adult red drum demonstrate fidelity to discrete
spawning areas. Stock assessment of red drum and spotted seatrout
requires information of exploitation, growth, fecundity (egg
production), angler harvest, and age structure.</p>

<p> <img src="art/green.gif"><a href="sst.htm"> Spotted Sea Trout </a></p>

<p> <img src="art/green.gif"><a href="drum.htm"> Red Drum</a></p>

<p> <img src="art/blue_bar.gif"></p>

<p> <a href="index.htm">Back to the CRD Homepage</a></p>

<p> </p>
</body>
</html>
