<body>

<h1>MARFIN Red Drum Tagging Project </h1>

<p> </p>

<h2>Recreational Fisheries Program</h2>

<p> Contact: Spud Woodward</p>

<p> Email: <a href="mailto:spud@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us">
spud@dnrcrd.dnr.state.ga.us </a></p>

<p> Phone: (912)264-7218</p>

<p> <img src="art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> MARFIN is a competitive grant program administered by the
National Marine Fisheries Service. This interstate project
involving Georgia, South Carolina, and North Carolina is titled
&quot; Fishery-independent Assessment of Subadult Red Drum in the
South Atlantic Bight&quot;. This was the first multi-state and
multi-year MARFIN grant awarded. The project period is from
September 1, 1994 thru August 31, 1997.</p>

<p> The objective of this project is to conduct regional
fishery-independent sampling and mark-recapture experiments to
provide the data needed for the assessment of South Atlantic
Bight (SAB) stocks of red drum. Stratified random sampling of
estuarine habitats used by red drum is being conducted in each of
the respective states using entanglement gear. Length-composition
and age-composition data are being compiled, reduced, and
analyzed to develop annual and cohort-specific mortality rates.
In addition, annual mark-recapture experiments will be used to
describe length-specific and age-specific vulnerability of red
drum within the recreational fishery. This project is being
conducted over a three year period in order to provide valid
estimates of mortality which are free of the effects of
recruitment variation. Data provided from this project will be
less biased than the fishery-dependent data currently used to
assess South Atlantic Bight red drum stocks. Any questions can be
directed to the Recreational Fisheries Program. </p>

<p> <img src="art/blue_bar.gif"></p>

<p> <a href="index.htm">Back to the CRD Homepage</a></p>

<p> </p>
</body>
