<body>

<h1>Saltwater/Freshwater Fishing Participation</h1>

<p> </p>

<h2>Nick Nicholson, Project Leader</h2>

<p> <img src="/CRD/art/blue_marble.gif"></p>

<p> To properly allocate Federal Aid in Sport Fish Restoration
funds between saltwater and freshwater anglers and to provide
data necessary to better manage Georgia's fishery resources, it
is essential to estmate numbers and determine the relative
percentages of resident Georgia saltwater and freshwater anglers
who fished within the state of Georgia during a specified period
of time. In the past, estimates of saltwater anglers were based
on an extremely small sample size; and the households that were
drawn by the U.S. Bureau of Census were not drawn based on the
population of anglers or angler households in the state, but
rather on some &quot;tiered&quot; sampling scheme which gives
metropolitan counties a high priority (i.e. all are selected),
and rural counties a low priority (few are selected). More
statistically valid estimates of participation are critical for
sound management decisions and proper fund allocations.</p>

<p> <img src="art/blue_bar.gif"></p>

<p> <a href="index.htm">Back to the CRD Homepage</a></p>

<p> </p>
</body>
